50|$|The {{regional}} flag {{shall be}} raised in mast at {{the left side of}} the Philippine flag. The distance between <b>the</b> <b>flags</b> <b>shall</b> be at least 2 meters apart from each other. The ARMM flag shall be raised one foot lower than the Philippine flag. It is mandatory for the flag to be displayed in educational institutions, public offices, government institutions and publicly owned corporations in the region. The flag may also be used for ceremonial and symbolic purposes and may be reproduced in smaller scales for such purposes.|$|E
50|$|If the intimation of {{the death}} of any {{dignitary}} is received in <b>the</b> afternoon, <b>the</b> <b>flag</b> <b>shall</b> be flown at halfmast on the following day also at the place or places indicated above, provided the funeral has not taken place before sunrise on that day. On the day of the funeral of a dignitary mentioned above, <b>the</b> <b>flag</b> <b>shall</b> be flown at half-mast at the place of the funeral.|$|R
